snippet.textDisplay:
So according to my wife: "I wouldn't watch it and here is why, Harley Quinn is a fascinating character and fro. What I understand Margot Robbies portrayal is spot on. However they never make a story worthy of her, Instead of writing a story that is commonplace and she is crazy in it they have to make everything else crazy around her. It makes me feel like I am watching a cartoon which makes the stakes that much sillier and thus I don't care about it all."

Which actually makes sense to me too, chew on that DC
Signed - the greatest Batman Fan Ever, and his wife....

See by saying "and his wife" at the end I make the point of exactly what you are doing in this movie with Harley Quinn, instead of making a movie dedicated to her you feel the need to involve a bunch of other female villans/heroes to cover up her story instead of just giving us the straight cocaine that is Harley.
Pity...

And his wife
